# Public Documentation Accuracy

## Canonical source

**[docs/SUPPORTED.md](../docs/SUPPORTED.md)** is the single source of truth for what is supported today vs on the roadmap.

When adding features, examples, or integration paths:

1. Update `docs/SUPPORTED.md` first (or in the same change).
2. Sync [README.md](../README.md) if the support matrix or status badges change.
3. Follow [docs-sync.mdc](./docs-sync.mdc) for package READMEs and `docs/INTEGRATION.md`.

## Wording rules (public repo)

| Do | Don't |
|----|-------|
| "Node.js 22+ (`@eudi-verify/server`)" for backend | "Any backend (PHP, Python, Java)" as if libraries exist |
| "Embeddable in any HTML page / SPA" for frontend | Imply WordPress plugin or Vue wrapper ships today |
| "OpenAPI contract — implement in any language" for non-Node backends | Hide that only Node handlers are published |
| Link to `docs/SUPPORTED.md` for full matrix | Scatter conflicting status in multiple files |
| Point React integration to `docs/wp/WP9.md` | Claim `@eudi-verify/react` ships before WP9 is done |

**Framework-agnostic** = no lock-in in core packages + OpenAPI contract. It is not a claim that every stack has a guide or npm package.

## Never in public docs

- Grant applications, funders, € amounts (see `PLAN.local.md` — private)

## Release checklist

Before a public release or major README change, verify:

- [ ] `docs/SUPPORTED.md` matches actual packages and examples
- [ ] README architecture / packages tables match `SUPPORTED.md`
- [ ] `docs/INTEGRATION.md` examples run (Node + html-vanilla at minimum)
- [ ] Demo-mode and production limitations are stated
